  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1221",
  "title": "Unable to define only one active/inactive showMore template",
  "body": "If I want to override the `active` or `inactive` templates of the `showMore` in a `refinementList`, it seems that I have to override both.\n\nIf I only supply `options.showMore.templates.active` or `options.showMore.templates.inactive`, then I'm greeted with `Uncaught Error: Template must be 'string' or 'function', was 'undefined' (key: show-more-inactive)`.\n\nThe workaround is to provide both templates, but the ideal fix would be to allow overriding only one of the two, and use the default value for the other one.\n\n``` javascript\ninstantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\n  showMore: {\n    templates: {\n      active: 'this will fail'\n      // inactive:'unless this is uncommented',\n    }\n  }\n})\n```\n",
